.TH "scal" "1" "" "" ""
.hy
.SH SCAL
.PP
cal, scal \- displays a calendar
.SH Synopsis
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
cal\ [[month]\ year]
scal\ [\-mycH3o:]\ [[month]\ year]
scal\ CALENDAR.scal
\f[]
.fi
.SH Description
.PP
The cal utility writes a calendar to the standard output.
The program supports categorizing days and coloring them.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[I]\-m\f[] : Monday first calendar.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[I]\-y\f[] : Display the full year.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[I]\-c\f[] : Force colored output.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[I]\-3\f[] : Display 3 months.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[I]\-L\f[] : Print a list, good for scripting.
.SH Options
.PP
Coloring can be defined in the \f[I]$SCAL_INFO\f[] environment variable,
the \f[I]$SCAL_FILE\f[], user \f[C]~/.config/calendar.scal\f[], system
\f[C]/etc/calendar.scal\f[] or the \f[C]\-o\f[] option.
Read \f[I]calendar.scal(5)\f[] manpage for more information.
